FXParticleSystem in a Nutshell\par
\i0\f2\fs18 The Particle System is triggered...\par
It waits 'InitialDelay' amount of seconds...\par
'BurstCount' amount of particles are released every 'BurstDelay' amount of time...\par
particles are set to 'Size' and size increases 'SizeRate', 'SizeRate is multiplied by 'SizeDamping'.....\par
particle rotation is set to 'AngleZ' and it increases 'AngularRateZ', 'AngularRateZ' is multiplied by 'AngularDamping'....\par
particles position is determined by 'EmissionVolume'....\par
particles velocity is determined by 'EmissionVelocity', that is multiplied by 'VelocityDamping'...\par
particles positon adds 'DriftVelocity' to its position, and Adds 'Gravity' to its ZLocation\par
If 'IsOneShot' and 'SystemLifetime' is up then System Dies, particles stop being produced and existing die.\i\f0\fs28\par
